00:08:45.300 --> 00:08:47.220
<v Speaker 1>I wanted them to do it.

00:08:47.220 --> 00:08:48.339
<v Speaker 1>I wanted that they do it.

00:08:50.259 --> 00:08:53.060
<v Speaker 1>How would you say I wanted for us to do it?

00:08:52.660 --> 00:08:54.580
<v Speaker 1>I wanted that we do it.

00:08:54.580 --> 00:08:57.460
<v Speaker 1>That we did it.

00:08:57.460 --> 00:09:00.740
<v Speaker 2>Caria Ke Lo Isieramos.

00:09:00.740 --> 00:09:01.780
<v Speaker 1>Good, well done.

00:09:01.780 --> 00:09:05.060
<v Speaker 1>Caria Ke Lo Isieramos.

00:09:05.060 --> 00:09:06.020
<v Speaker 1>Good.

00:09:06.020 --> 00:09:13.540
<v Speaker 1>I'm not as interested here in installing, let's say, all of this content, all of these irregular verbs.

00:09:13.540 --> 00:09:15.860
<v Speaker 1>What I want to give you is an exposure

00:09:16.140 --> 00:09:23.660
<v Speaker 1>To how they might work, the irregular verbs that you can come across, so that practicing you can manage them.

00:09:23.660 --> 00:09:28.300
<v Speaker 1>So you should not be afraid of making mistakes, you should build the verbs

